1. Mathematical Foundations

1.1 Notation and Definitions

Let:

· \mathcal{O} = orbital parameters (altitude h, inclination i, beta angle \beta)
· \Phi(t) = solar flux at time t (W/m²)
· A_r = radiator area (m²), A_s = solar array area (m²)
· T_s(t) = radiator surface temperature (K), T_{env}(t) = environmental temperature (K)
· P_c(t) = computational power (W), P_s(t) = solar power harvested (W)
· Q_{pcm}(t) = latent heat stored in PCM (J)
· E_b(t) = battery energy (J)

Definition 1.1 (Orbital State). The orbital state o(t) \in \mathbb{R}^4 is:

o(t) = [\Phi(t), T_{env}(t), \lambda_{SEE}(t), \beta_{sun}(t)]^T

where \lambda_{SEE} is radiation flux and \beta_{sun} is Sun aspect angle.

Definition 1.2 (System State). The OCN state x(t) \in \mathbb{R}^4:

x(t) = [T_c(t), E_b(t), Q_{pcm}(t), W_q(t)]^T

where W_q is queued work (TFLOPS-hr).

