1.3 State-Space Formulation

1.3.1 Continuous Dynamics

The OCN dynamics are:

\frac{dx}{dt} = f(x(t), u(t), o(t))

where u(t) \in \mathbb{R}^5 is the control vector:

u(t) = [f_{clk}(t), V_{dd}(t), m_{migrate}(t), P_{rad,active}(t), u_{mit}(t)]^T

System Dynamics:

1. Thermal:

\frac{dT_c}{dt} = \frac{1}{C_{th}} \left[P_c(u) + \alpha A_s \Phi(t) - \epsilon \sigma A_r (T_c^4 - T_{env}^4) - \frac{dQ_{pcm}}{dt}\right]

1. Battery:

\frac{dE_b}{dt} = \eta_{charge} \cdot \eta_{pv} A_s \Phi(t) - \frac{P_c(u)}{\eta_{discharge}} - P_{house}

where \eta_{pv} is PV efficiency, \eta_{charge/discharge} are battery efficiencies.

1. PCM (Phase Change Material):

\frac{dQ_{pcm}}{dt} = 
\begin{cases}
\min(P_{net}, (Q_{max} - Q_{pcm})/\tau) & \text{if } T_c \geq T_{melt} \text{ and } P_{net} > 0 \\
\max(P_{net}, -Q_{pcm}/\tau) & \text{if } T_c \leq T_{melt} \text{ and } P_{net} < 0 \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}

where P_{net} = P_c + \alpha A_s \Phi - \epsilon \sigma A_r (T_c^4 - T_{env}^4), Q_{max} = m_{pcm} L, and \tau is phase change time constant.

1. Work Queue:

\frac{dW_q}{dt} = - \frac{\eta_{compute} P_c(u)}{E_{per\_FLOP}} + \lambda_{arrival}(t)

where E_{per\_FLOP} is energy per FLOP, \lambda_{arrival} is work arrival rate.

