1.4 Optimal Control Formulation

1.4.1 Finite-Horizon Optimization

Problem 1.1 (OCN Optimal Control). Given initial state x_0 and orbital predictions o(\tau) for \tau \in [t, t+H], find control sequence u^*(\tau) that maximizes:

J = \int_t^{t+H} \left[ \alpha \text{TFLOPS}(u(\tau)) - \beta (T_c - T_{target})^2 - \gamma \text{Penalty}(x, u) \right] d\tau

subject to:

1. T_{min} \leq T_c(\tau) \leq T_{max}
2. E_b(\tau) \geq E_{min}
3. \int_t^{t+H} P_c(\tau) d\tau \leq \int_t^{t+H} \eta_{pv} A_s \Phi(\tau) d\tau + \Delta E_{batt,max}
4. \text{MTBF}_{eff} \geq \text{MTBF}_{req}

