1.6.2 Thermal Time Constant with PCM

Lemma 1.3 (Effective Thermal Mass). With PCM, the effective thermal time constant \tau_{eff} is:

\tau_{eff} = \tau_{th} + \frac{m_{pcm}L}{P_{avg}}

where \tau_{th} = C_{th}/hA is the bare thermal time constant.

Proof. During phase change, the system appears to have infinite heat capacity. The additional time to absorb heat Q = m_{pcm}L at rate P_{avg} is Q/P_{avg}. ∎

