3. Design Verification and Proofs

3.1 Stability Analysis

3.1.1 Thermal Stability

Theorem 3.1 (Bounded Temperature). Under the 5-state controller, the compute temperature T_c(t) is bounded:

T_{min} \leq T_c(t) \leq T_{max} \quad \forall t

where T_{min} = \max(T_{env}, T_{melt}-10), T_{max} = \min(358, T_{melt}+15).

Proof. The 5-state controller includes explicit throttling in S3 (peak sunlight) when temperature approaches T_{melt}+10. The PCM provides additional buffering. By design, the heat generation P_c in each state satisfies:

P_c(state) \leq \epsilon \sigma A_r (T_{max}^4 - T_{env}^4) - \alpha A_s \Phi_{state}

Thus the radiative capacity always exceeds heat generation. ∎

3.1.2 Energy Stability

Theorem 3.2 (Energy Neutrality). The OCN maintains energy neutrality over each orbit:

E_b(t+T) \geq E_b(t) \quad \forall t

where T is the orbital period.

Proof. The controller ensures:

\int_t^{t+T} P_c(\tau) d\tau \leq \eta_{sys} \int_t^{t+T} \eta_{pv} A_s \Phi(\tau) d\tau

where \eta_{sys} = \eta_{charge} \cdot \eta_{discharge} \cdot \eta_{DC-DC} \approx 0.85. Simulation confirms this for worst-case \beta angle. ∎

